FAQ S - Splitero How it works About us FAQ X Get my cash estimate Get my estimate Call us How it works About us FAQ X Get my estimate Getting Started With Splitero Splitero’s Offer General All FAQS Frequently asked questions What are the basic property requirements to qualify for a Splitero investment? In order to be eligible for a Splitero investment, the subject property must be located in an eligible area and have an appraised value between $150,000 - $5,000 Properties that may be eligible for a Splitero investment include: residence Condominiums Townhomes Properties with units Owner occupied and occupied Held by individuals, in trusts (subject to approval), and by LLCs (subject to approval) Properties with 5 or more units if occupied Modular Manufactured Prefabricated Log cabins Houseboats Homes with nontraditional design (e.g. geodesic, earth berm, constructed from a shipping container) Commercial Agricultural use case properties Properties that are not eligible for a Splitero investment include: Properties located on 5 or more acres Timeshares, fractional or segmented ownership Will my credit be pulled, what type of pull is it, and is there a minimum credit score requirement? There is no minimum credit During the process, we will run a soft inquiry on your A soft inquiry does not affect your credit At the time of application, we will pull your credit which will result in a hard Your credit report will remain valid for days from the date it is How long will it take for a homeowner to be notified of an approval decision? Once a full application has been submitted, you may receive an approval decision in as little as one Once a homeowner is approved, we will then determine the eligibility of the home to ensure it meets Splitero’s minimum investment In some situations, homeowners receive their Splitero Offer in as little as one day from the application approval How long will it take to get my funds? Once you are approved, you may receive your funds in as little as fourteen (14) Are second homes or investment properties eligible? Yes, Splitero invests in occupied Is my property eligible if it is held in a trust? Properties held in trust are eligible for a Splitero You will need to provide documentation on your trust prior to receiving full application How much money can I get from Splitero? Splitero offers investments up to $500 We will take your credit history and home equity position into consideration when determining the offer The minimum equity a homeowner must retain in the home after the investment is %. Click here to for a Splitero investment! It takes less than 2 minutes to see how much you may qualify Am I eligible if I have an existing reverse mortgage or another shared equity agreement? You may be eligible as long as you pay off your reverse mortgage or shared equity agreement before or through the closing of your Splitero Click here to see if the amount you may qualify for will be sufficient to pay off an existing When and how is my home’s value determined? As part of your application review, we will determine the value of your home, which will be known as the Appraised Based on factors related to your home and application, an adjustment will be applied and discounted from the Appraised Value to determine the Starting When you are ready to repay Splitero, we will complete another evaluation of your home to determine the Ending All evaluations of your home will be through a provider such as a licensed appraiser or another valuation You may use the calculator below to estimate the repayment amount based on different What if I don’t agree with the appraised value? If you don’t agree with the Appraised Value, you may contact your designated Homeowner Advisor and they will advise you on the available options to have your home value What are the fees associated with an investment from Splitero? Fees associated with a Splitero investment are charged upon closing and will be deducted from your investment Please keep this in mind when determining the net amount of money you would like to receive from Here is a breakdown of estimated costs: Service Estimated Cost Origination Fee % of the Gross Investment amount, or a minimum of $1,500 Appraisal $200-700 Payoff Demand Statement $30 Title $200-900 Escrow $250-550 The above breakdown is the estimated costs charged by Splitero and or its service It is not an exclusive list of costs and does not include costs incurred from your current lender or by your state or Can I buy back my equity? Yes, you may buy back your equity at any time during the Buybacks typically occur via either a refinance or a cash Can I repay Splitero through the sale of my home? Yes, you can repay Splitero through the closing of your The sale must be an arm’s length transaction at fair market Are there any prepayment penalties? You can repay Splitero at any time during the There is no prepayment penalty! What is the maximum potential cost of a Splitero Investment? Every Splitero investm

Blog We re Hiring Serverless database for Jamstack, , and more Xata is a combination of a relational database, an analytics engine, and a search All made simple by a UI and a single powerful data API , with granular security, migrations, subscriptions, ACID transactions, and caching Coming soon . Want to be notified when we launch? Keep me in the loop WORKS WITH ANY FAAS PROVIDER No servers, No Ops, No Stress! If you don’t worry about servers when deploying your application, why should you worry about servers (or nodes, or clusters) when using a database service? The simple global RESTful API for inserting, querying, aggregating, and searching makes Xata the perfect companion for Serverless and Low-Code development Connectionless API Scales automatically Pay as you go No operations UI Xata allows you to iteratively build your database schema as you add sample data, all via a UI . You can add new tables, columns, data, and create queries and It then gives you code samples ready to be used in your This gives you flexibility as you develop and, as the application grows, the strict schema keeps your data safe and correct . Developer workflow with branches Xata is the first database service designed to match your development Create branches for your Push to deploy, preview, and Merge to deploy to Creating deleting branches is almost instantaneous, and we migrate your data with zero Manage multiple environments Manage schema migrations Tighter change controls for prod Ideal for Jamstack With database branches as a first class citizen and our deep integrations, Xata is the ideal companion for platforms like Netlify and It’s equally easy to query the database at Static Generation time (SSG), when using Rendering (SSR), or when using The CDN caching makes querying the database as fast and efficient as querying the CDN for static Flexible security rules Use the UI to define which users can access the data and under which Then we generate the secure APIs for you, so you can focus on the This frees you from having to write boilerplate CRUD backends over and over Or, if you prefer, use serverless functions as your The choice is Free text Search In today’s world, almost any application requires powerful and relevant Why integrate with and pay for multiple services when you can get the functionality that you need all in one? No more copying data between the DB and the search Fine tune relevance controls Analytics Aggregations and facets are a key part of almost any Active users over time, top paying customers, most reviewed entries, number of reviews over time, the number of products in each Create visualizations with the GUI, then click the “View code” icon to see the API Fast aggregations at any scale No complicated SQL to create aggregations Our Investors Xata is backed by investors and angels with a lot of experience in the infrastracture space, including the founders and leaders of several unicorn Shay Banon & CEO, Elastic Uri Boness , Elastic Neha Narkhede , Confluent Guillermo Rauch Founder & CEO, Vercel Stephanie Friedman Board of Directors, Apollo GraphQL Elad Gil , Color Genomics Christian Bach & , Netlify Liu Jiang Ex Sequoia Partner Mathias Biilmann & , Netlify Charlie Songhurst Ex Head of Corporate Strategy, Microsoft Keenan Rice VP Strategic Alliances, Looker We’re hiring! We all work remotely, usually from home, and we meet in person a couple of times per year in a nice We believe in and clean code, simple tools, progress over perfection, and addressing technical debt early . We also put a lot of value on balance and you should expect a relaxed, diverse, and inclusive work View Open Positions Xata offers a serverless database service that combines the power of a traditional database with the usability of a SaaS spreadsheet Get in touch Twitter Linkedin Email Keep me in the loop:   Xata | Hello, World! Exai Bio Press Contact Us Exai Bio Secures $67.5 Million Series A December 9, San Francisco, CA Exai Bio, a liquid biopsy company, today announced it has raised a $67.5 million Series A financing to accelerate development of its , liquid biopsy platform for early cancer The financing was led by leading life sciences and tech investors Section and Casdin Capital , with participation from Two Sigma Ventures , who have been integral to advancing cancer diagnostics and artificial intelligence machine learning Exai Bioâs platform delivers unprecedented clinical insight into cancer biology from blood samples enabling early and accurate diagnosis of cancer to inform personalized care Unlike first generation liquid biopsy tests which measure circulating tumor DNA (ctDNA) mutations and or epigenetic markers (such as ctDNA methylation or fragmentation patterns), Exai Bioâs proprietary platform measures RNA profiles, analyzing them using advanced artificial intelligence and machine learning Specifically, Exai Bio is focused on orphan RNA (oncRNA), small RNA sequences not seen in normal tissue but abundant in In liquid biopsy samples, these oncRNAs translate to higher sensitivity and specificity, ultimately enabling a more accurate diagnosis as compared to liquid biopsy Exai Bioâs approach is applicable across multiple unmet needs in âExai Bio is the first company founded to explore the important role of oncRNA in early and more accurate cancer detection and its important impact on improved patient outcomes and health economics,â said Patrick Arensdorf, chief executive officer, Exai âCombining oncRNA technology with machine learning and artificial intelligence to decipher tumor signals and understand the active biology of disease, Exai Bioâs next generation liquid biopsy platform provides actionable information to help inform accurate clinical  Exai Bioâs next generation liquid biopsy platform was developed based on groundbreaking research Koala Health makes it easy to shop for all of your pet’s medications and health related products and provides you with free services that simplify the medication management Those free services include: : you never have to worry about running out of your pet’s medications Prescription management: we work with your vet to make sure your pet’s prescriptions always have refills Pouch packaging: we sort your pet’s medications by date and time into individual pouches so you never have to worry about which medications to give when or if you or your partner already gave your pet their What is a Pet Care Box? Pick a language, write your code, and compile it to But what kinds of code does one write in WebAssembly? The original way to run a WebAssembly module was in the For that reason, early WebAssembly effort was focused on optimizing code to be executed on a web page or web WebAssembly has now moved beyond the Some platforms, like the Envoy proxy, allow you to write plugins in Wasm . Command line runtimes like Wasmtime and WAMR run Wasm binaries on the command line, allowing developers to write a single CLI application that can run on Windows, macOS, and Linux (regardless of the underlying architecture). Here at Fermyon, we are most excited about the prospect of writing microservices and web applications in We gave a preview of this when we built But with Spin, we’re taking things to a new Most specifically, Spin offers a framework for building What do we mean when we talk about a “framework”? A framework provides a set of features and conventions that assist a developer in reaching their desired goal faster and with less Ruby on Rails and Python Django are two good Spin is a framework for web apps, microservices, and other It provides the interfaces for writing WebAssembly modules that can do things like answer HTTP One unique thing about Spin is that it is a Rust and Go both have robust support in Spin, but you can also write Python, Ruby, AssemblyScript, Grain, C C++, and other We are excited to already be using Spin in The Spin docs are (appropriately enough) running on That website is powered by the Bartholomew CMS system and is running on an HA Nomad cluster . biology of regulatory T cells (Tregs) into transformational medicines for patients with progressive multiple sclerosis and other serious autoimmune and inflammatory diseases Who We Are Abata was launched in by Third Rock Ventures with a $95 million Series A financing and brings together industry experts and deeply engaged pioneers in regulatory T cell (Treg) biology, T cell receptor (TCR) and antigen discovery, disease pathogenesis, and molecular and imaging biomarkers to advance the development of Treg cell therapies for serious autoimmune and inflammatory Together, we are bringing an entirely new approach to the treatment of autoimmune disease by engineering Tregs as targeted therapies that stop destruction, restore homeostasis – a state of harmony – and promote repair in the affected It’s all in the name Abata’s story begins with our In Nyanja, a Bantu language widely spoken in southern Africa, “abata” means “tranquil,” and “ndi malo abata” translates to “it’s a quiet ” In Esperanto, “abata” means “of an abbey,” a place of “Abata” is the very essence of what our Treg cell therapies seek to do: restore tranquility, peace and harmony in the Leadership Samantha Singer, harnessing the immune system’s natural ability to fight By understanding the intricate mechanisms by which these cells contribute to disease, we are developing innovative immunotherapies that target the root causes of cardiovascular disease rather than just treating its Our approach is grounded in scientific research and close collaboration with cardiologists to ensure the safety and efficacy of our therapies for Our ultimate goal is to provide new hope to those suffering from cardiovascular disease and transform the way these diseases are Atherosclerosis: AN INFLAMMATORY DISEASE Atherosclerosis is a complex inflammatory disease that is characterized by the accumulation of fatty deposits, or “plaques,” in the walls of the Plaques are made up of cholesterol, lipids, and other substances that cause the arteries to narrow and harden, making it difficult for blood to flow through Atherosclerotic plaque formation is a dynamic biological process perpetuated by Inflammation in blood vessel plaque triggers an immune Immune cells and circulating factors called “cytokines” further increase inflammation and the buildup of dead, or necrotic, debris within the vessel This vicious cycle of inflammation contributes to the evolution and further maturation of the atherosclerotic Over time, some plaques may destabilize and rupture, triggering the formation of a clot within the lumen of an These clots can suddenly block blood flow to healthy heart or brain tissue, leading to a cardiovascular We believe that it is possible to prevent atherosclerotic plaques from progressing by targeting CD47, a widely expressed cellular receptor well known for its immunoregulatory This bold and novel therapeutic approach is being investigated to reduce the incidence of debilitating heart attacks and THE ROLE OF CD47 CD47 is a protein that is expressed on the surface of cells and acts as a potent “don’t eat me” Its presence enables harmful cells to avoid immune cells such as By evading detection and destruction by the immune system, these harmful cells join a growing plaque within the arterial Recent research has shown that CD47 levels are elevated in the walls of blood vessels of patients with atherosclerosis and that this elevation is associated with an increased risk of heart attack and Further studies have revealed that blocking CD47 can enhance macrophage activity and r

A learning disability, also referred to as a learning disorder, is an problem that prevents a person from learning a skill and using it Learning disabilities generally affect people of average or above average As a result, the disability appears as a gap between expected skills, based on age and intelligence, and academic Common learning disabilities affect a child s abilities in reading, written expression, math or nonverbal (Source: Mayo Clinic ) What is dyslexia? and Chairman of “We look forward to partnering with Interfirst’s talented management team and employees to help accelerate the realization of Interfirst’s ” "We are thrilled to welcome StoicLane as our new partner, as Al and the team share our strategic vision for the ,” said Dmitry Godin, CEO of “StoicLane’s investment in Interfirst signifies their confidence in our commitment to innovate and deliver technology for the mortgage This partnership will help us continue to build as we drive the mortgage industry ” ​ Brian Laibow, Managing Director and of North America for Oaktree’s Global Workflows are a sequence of serverless Workflows can run automatically (each time an event is received), on a schedule, or manually via forms (in the case of internal tools, or ). Workflows allow you to chain logic together, coordinate between events, and create complex user flows and operational logic for your A simple workflow might only run one single serverless function this is still a Do you charge for events? We re currently accepting all events, Our "soft" limit is events mo across free and paid plans, and from events mo on custom We don t throttle you, right What resources are available? Free accounts are limited to of ram and a maximum runtime of seconds per Paid accounts can utilize of ram and have a runime limit of seconds per Advanced accounts can use up to of ram and can run functions for up to 6 hours if you need this functionality get in touch with us . What if I need to run more functions? That s okay! We ll alert you when you re nearing your cap and will throttle your workflows after hitting the You can always purchase more capacity, but we won t apply overage fees unless you specify payment caps (coming soon). We dislike surprise costs as much as You can buy an extra ,000 runs for $10. Event coordination allows you to wait for specific events from within a For example, after creating a shopping cart you might want to wait for the "order created" event for up to If this event is received, the person who created the shopping cart checked If the event isn t received within hours, you can run logic to handle We allow you to coordinate between events and wait up to 6 months for new That s... quite some Are there limits to how complex I can make a workflow? No, not You can chain hundreds of functions in parallel we ll run it for Is there a limit to how often I can run scheduled workflows?
